        <hr noshade size="2" color="#545A7D">
        
         There are several ways to fear kite of course, it just takes practice to get good at it.</P><P>This is how I like to fear kite...</P><P>1) Pull the mob with darkness (on the non-long runs)<BR>2) Run far enough to not get hit when I get back and cast fear<BR>3) Send pet, he doesn't take any damage so far and this should keep him alive longer in case of resists<BR>4) BoD (any leech line works, just depends on your level)</P><P>Thats about it, always keep a HP to mana spell up, use your leech line to counter the HP taken and if you have to, drain you way back up.</P><P><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=278788"><img src="http://baritz.freeservers.com/baritz.jpg"></a><a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
